<p><a id=\"skills\"></a></p>
<h3><strong>Skills</strong></h3>
<hr />
<p><strong>Scripting, Data Analysis and Visualization</strong><br />
MATLAB, Microsoft Excel  </p>
<p><strong>Web Technologies</strong><br />
HTML, CSS, TWIG, YAML, WordPress, Grav  </p>
<p><strong>Databases and CRM Tools</strong><br />
Siebel, Salesforce</p>
<p>MATLAB has been my <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_of_the_instrument\">hammer</a> for a good part of my career, and I have used it for much of my computing and scripting needs. MATLAB was my tool of choice for much of my doctoral dissertation and Masters thesis work. I have used, and continue to use, MATLAB for scientific computing, data wrangling, analysis and visualization of large datasets, scripting, text analytics, web scraping, and working with robotic and hardware systems.</p>
<p>I am deeply fascinated by the growth of interactive web tools for engaging storytelling (think <a href=\"https://fivethirtyeight.com/\">FiveThirtyEight</a> and <a href=\"http://www.informationisbeautiful.net\">information is beautiful</a>) My current pursuits, this website included, are focused on creating a space for interactive data stories on civic governance, smart cities and the use of technology and data for social good. I am currently learning D3.js and other charting libraries to this effect.</p>
<p><a id=\"workex\"></a></p>
<h3><strong>Work Experience</strong></h3>
<hr />
<h5><strong>Education Technical Evangelist</strong></h5>
<p>MathWorks<br />
Sep. 2013 – present  </p>
<p>Worked closely with STEM educators at leading higher education universities, supporting computational and curriculum needs with MATLAB towards enhancing undergraduate learning.</p>
<h6>Internal accomplishments</h6>
<ul>
<li>Played a key role in increasing awareness and adoption of MathWorks products within the academic community.</li>
<li>Created technical and presentation content for self-paced workshops on autograding solutions and the use of low-cost hardware and smartphone sensors for project-based learning.</li>
</ul>
<h6>Customer Interactions</h6>
<ul>
<li>Provided close technical guidance to over 500 educators over one-on-one interactions, on incorporating computational content, autograding workflow and project-based learning in teaching.    </li>
<li>Delivered presentations and workshops at conferences to promote computational thinking, use of technology in pedagogy, and teaching with hardware (Raspberry Pi, LEGO, Android/iOS devices) and smartphone sensors in higher education.</li>
</ul>
<h5><strong>Entrepreneurial Lead</strong></h5>
<p>NSF I-Corps Program<br />
Jun. 2013 – Aug. 2013  </p>
<ul>
<li>Investigated the market potential for commercialization of doctoral research on the use of unmanned aerial vehicles for wildland fire monitoring.</li>
<li>Held discussions with over 100 federal, state and commercial agencies towards requirement and technical feasibility assessment. </li>
</ul>
<h5><strong>Research Assistant</strong></h5>
<p>Co-Operative Distributed Systems Laboratory, University of Cincinnati<br />
Sep. 2009 – Jun. 2013  </p>
<ul>
<li>Developed and experimentally implemented a novel cyclic pursuit algorithm in a multi-agent ground-robot system for cooperative perimeter tracking.</li>
<li>Developed a low-dimensional Kalman-filter based spatio-temporal estimation method for monitoring and predicting the growth of forest fires.</li>
<li>Led efforts towards the establishment of an experimental facility for developing and implementing multi-robot distributed navigation and control algorithms. Hardware setup included ground and aerial robotic platforms, a motion tracking system, and wireless communications with remote PC.</li>
</ul>
